# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Resend — early-access email capture (free study-guide delivery)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used by app/api/subscribe (server-side only). These are SECRET — never prefix
# with NEXT_PUBLIC_, which would expose the key in the browser.
#
# Until ALL THREE are set, the form shows a "sign-ups aren't switched on yet"
# message instead of collecting emails. Set them locally in .env.local, and in
# your host's env settings (e.g. Vercel) before the site goes live.
#
#   RESEND_API_KEY      Resend dashboard -> API Keys
#   RESEND_AUDIENCE_ID  Resend dashboard -> Audiences -> (your audience) -> ID
#   RESEND_FROM         Sender on a Resend-VERIFIED domain, e.g.
#                       "Navo <hello@navolearning.com>"
#
# The welcome email attaches public/study-guide.pdf by URL, so the deployed site
# must be reachable for the attachment to fetch (it can't attach from localhost).
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_AUDIENCE_ID=
RESEND_FROM=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Search Console (optional) — site-verification meta tag
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Paste the token from Search Console's "HTML tag" verification method. When set,
# Next renders <meta name="google-site-verification" ...>. Safe to leave blank.
GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=
